GPIO 33 is the NeoPixel data pin; GPIO 21 is the NeoPixel power-enable (active HIGH). Bring power high before writing colors, hold it for 100 us, then write the WS2812 sequence on GPIO 33.

```cpp
#include <Adafruit_NeoPixel.h>
const int NEO_PIN = 33;
const int NEO_POWER = 21;
Adafruit_NeoPixel pixel(1, NEO_PIN, NEO_GRB + NEO_KHZ800);

void setup() {
  pinMode(NEO_POWER, OUTPUT);
  digitalWrite(NEO_POWER, HIGH);
  pixel.begin();
  pixel.setBrightness(40);
  pixel.setPixelColor(0, pixel.Color(0, 255, 0));
  pixel.show();
}

void loop() {}
```

Disable the power pin during sleep to save 1-2 mA. The on-board pixel is a single GRB WS2812 inside the silver dome.
